      <TextArea layoutX="34.0" layoutY="48.0" prefHeight="530.0" prefWidth="884.0" style="-fx-background-radius: 10; -fx-background-color: #98DD98;" text="Driving on the Left:&#10;In Bangladesh, vehicles should be driven on the left side of the road.&#10;&#10;Traffic Signals and Signs:&#10;Adhere to traffic signals, signs, and road markings. Follow the instructions given by traffic police.&#10;&#10;Speed Limits:&#10;Observe speed limits specified for different types of roads. Speeding is a common cause of accidents, so it's essential to drive within the prescribed limits.&#10;&#10;Overtaking Rules:&#10;Overtake only when it is safe and legal to do so. Avoid overtaking in areas with poor visibility, intersections, and pedestrian crossings.&#10;&#10;Seat Belts:&#10;Both the driver and passengers are required to wear seat belts. It is crucial for safety and is enforced by law.&#10;&#10;Mobile Phones:&#10;Using mobile phones while driving is often prohibited or restricted. It is safer to pull over if you need to make a call or send a message.&#10;&#10;Drinking and Driving:&#10;Driving under the influence of alcohol or drugs is strictly prohibited. There are strict penalties for drunk driving offenses.&#10;&#10;Helmet Usage:&#10;Motorcyclists and their passengers are often required to wear helmets. This is a safety measure to protect against head injuries.&#10;&#10;Horn Usage:&#10;Use the horn judiciously. In some areas, unnecessary honking is penalized, especially during the night.&#10;&#10;Lane Discipline:&#10;Follow lane discipline and stay within your lane. Avoid abrupt lane changes and maintain a safe distance from the vehicle in front.">
